'''Shōshoi''' (少初位), also known as '''Oshisaka no Hikohito no Ōe no Miko''' (押坂彦人大兄皇子, [[生没年不詳]]), was a member of the imperial family during the [[Asuka period]]. He was also referred to as '''Oshisaka no Hikohito Prince''', '''Maroko Prince''', '''Taishi Hikohito Prince''', '''Oshisaka Hikohito Taishi''', and '''Ōso Taishi'''. He was the first son of '''{{ill|Emperor Bidatsu|ja|敏達天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Bidatsu|qq=}}''' and his consort, {{ill|Hirohime|ja|広姫|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hirohime|qq=}}. His children include '''{{ill|Emperor Jomei|ja|舒明天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Jomei|qq=}}''' and {{ill|Prince Chinu|ja|茅渟王|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prince Chinu|qq=}}.
The modern {{ill|Imperial House of Japan|ja|皇室|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imperial House of Japan|qq=}} is descended in the male line from Shōshoi.
== Life == Born as the first son of {{ill|Emperor Bidatsu|ja|敏達天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Bidatsu|qq=}}, his mother was {{ill|Hirohime|ja|広姫|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hirohime|qq=}}, daughter of {{ill|Prince Okinaga Makoto|ja|息長真手王|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prince Okinaga Makoto|qq=}}.
Shōshoi was a prominent figure of the Bidatsu lineage, which was unconnected to the Soga clan. He maintained independent financial bases such as the {{ill|Oshisaka|ja|忍坂部|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Oshisaka|qq=}} and {{ill|Maroko|ja|丸子部|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Maroko|qq=}} estates and resided outside the royal capital at the Mimata Palace (水派宮), likely located in {{ill|Kōryō, Nara|ja|奈良県河合町|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōryō, Nara|qq=}}. After the death of {{ill|Emperor Yōmei|ja|用明天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Yōmei|qq=}} in [[587]], he was considered a potential heir to the throne. However, the rise of the Soga clan resulted in his disappearance from historical records. Some speculate he was {{ill|assassinated|ja|暗殺|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/assassinated|qq=}}<ref>Speculations include assassination during the [[587]] conflict between the Soga and Mononobe clans ({{ill|Yukihisa Yamano|ja|山尾幸久|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yukihisa Yamano|qq=}}) or an accidental death ({{ill|Hajime Wada|ja|和田萃|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hajime Wada|qq=}}), but there is no historical evidence.</ref>. Nevertheless, based on records in the ''{{ill|Ichidai Yōki|ja|一代要記|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ichidai Yōki|qq=}}'' and ''{{ill|Shōunroku|ja|紹運録|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōunroku|qq=}}'', and the birth year of {{ill|Emperor Jomei|ja|舒明天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Jomei|qq=}} (593), it is believed Shōshoi survived until after [[592]], during the reign of {{ill|Empress Suiko|ja|推古天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Empress Suiko|qq=}}.
His private estates, including those inherited by his son Emperor Jomei, provided significant financial support for non-Soga claimants to the throne. These estates, called "Imperial Grand Progenitor Named Divisions," were later returned to the state following the {{ill|Taika Reforms|ja|大化の改新|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taika Reforms|qq=}} (645).
== Genealogy == Based on the ''{{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kojiki|qq=}}'': * Consort: {{ill|Ohari Princess|ja|小墾田皇女|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ohari Princess|qq=}}, daughter of Emperor Bidatsu and Empress Suiko * Consort: {{ill|Sakurai Yumihari Princess|ja|桜井弓張皇女|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sakurai Yumihari Princess|qq=}} ''' Children: Prince Yamashiro, Prince Kasanu * Consort: {{ill|Nukatehime Princess|ja|糠手姫皇女|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nukatehime Princess|qq=}} ''' Children: {{ill|Emperor Jomei|ja|田村王|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Jomei|qq=}}, Prince Nakatsu, {{ill|Prince Tara|ja|多良王|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prince Tara|qq=}} * Consort: {{ill|Ōmata Princess|ja|大俣女王|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōmata Princess|qq=}}, sister of {{ill|Prince Kan|ja|漢王|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prince Kan|qq=}} ''' Children: {{ill|Prince Chinu|ja|茅渟王|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prince Chinu|qq=}}, Princess Kuwata
=== Descendants === Shōshoi's descendants, including Emperor Jomei, played pivotal roles in the continuation of the non-Soga lineage during the Asuka period.
